Conversely , early “ unplugged ” versions of “ The Long and Winding Road ” featured none of the orchestral flourishes later added in final production before the record was finally released . The question begs asking : Do these alternate incarnations of songs , no matter how creatively interesting , really resonate with anyone who is n’t a devotee of the band ’s music ?
